# Hosting Overview

Platform: Render (Cloud PaaS)

Service:
  - Spring Boot REST API
  - Deployed via Docker container
  - Public endpoint: https://csce548.onrender.com

Database:
  - PostgreSQL (Render Managed Database)
  - Accessed via JDBC
  - Environment variables used for credentials

Testing:
  - ConsoleApp demonstrates full CRUD lifecycle.

I will switch hosts in the future. I decided to use Render because they had a postgres host but it will be deleted in a month...

# How to Run the Plant Tracker Service

====================================
1. Running Locally (Development)
====================================

Prerequisites:
- Java 17+
- Maven
- PostgreSQL installed locally

Step 1: Create a local PostgreSQL database

Open SQL Shell (psql):

CREATE DATABASE plantdb;

Connect to it:

\c plantdb

Run the table creation script:

\i db_creation_postgres.sql


Step 2: Set Environment Variables (optional)

If not set, default values will be used.

Windows PowerShell:
setx PLANTDB_URL "jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/plantdb"
setx PLANTDB_USER "postgres"
setx PLANTDB_PASS "yourpassword"

Restart terminal after setting variables.


Step 3: Start Spring Boot Application

From project root:

mvn clean package
mvn spring-boot:run

Service runs at:
http://localhost:8080

Test endpoint:
http://localhost:8080/api/plants


====================================
2. Running in the Cloud (Render)
====================================

The application is deployed on Render.

Public URL:
https://csce548.onrender.com

Deployment steps:

1. Push code to GitHub.
2. Create Web Service on Render (Docker).
3. Create PostgreSQL database on Render.
4. Configure environment variables:
   - PLANTDB_URL
   - PLANTDB_USER
   - PLANTDB_PASS
5. Deploy.
6. Create tables using db_creation_postgres.sql.


====================================
3. Running the Console Test Client
====================================

The console application tests full CRUD functionality.

It performs:
- Create plant
- Read plant
- Update plant
- Delete plant

Run using Maven:

mvn compile exec:java


The console client connects to:
https://csce548.onrender.com

To change the URL:

Windows:
setx PLANT_SERVICE_URL "http://localhost:8080"

Mac/Linux:
export PLANT_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:8080
